<br>
By default, the players name is hard coded to be displayed with the players health bar. In some mods, the text for the name is offset so that it is hidden though.  This means you do not have to add a second &lt;EQType&gt;1&lt;/EQType&gt; tag in the player window, its already there.<br>
<br>
If you added a second &lt;EQType&gt;1&lt;/EQType&gt; to the player window then the playername in the inventory wil not display. Remove the second &lt;EQType&gt;1&lt;/EQType&gt; tag in the player window and find the &lt;TextOffsetX&gt; of the first &lt;EQType&gt;1&lt;/EQType&gt; in the player window, it should be under the &lt;Gauge item = &quot;Player_HP&quot;&gt; field near the top.  Set the offset to something like 8 and it should display. <p><center><b>~ Baroness Tippwindy Ayreheart ~<br>
